@{ui}
I've agree to the point that I only watch most sci-fi shows once and end up
never watching them again.  It might be because I'm twisted but I enjoy
"Lost in Space" re-runs, I can't think why when I turn off startrek <insert
startrek spin off here> the moment it comes on.  I think the reason the
XFiles has been such a cult is it's reasonably good scripts and it's
excellent photography, but the sceptic/believer scenario between Moulder and
Scully is wearing a little thin now, it also doesn't rely on special effects
which can't be too bad a thing.


