On Tue, 30 Jan 1996, Mikael Johannsen wrote:

@{i}> Hi.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> How do you make an object completly transparent without changing every
@{ui}@{i}> attribute to zero in every child obejct?
@{ui}@{i}> I tried the transpar.itx with apply to children, but that only made my
@{ui}@{i}> object half transparent. Why is that?
@{ui}
That's because all Transpar does is move the color values of your object
into the filter slots, making your object sort of transparent, but not
quite.

