@node 0078 "Message number 0078"

@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Fri, 2 Feb 1996 08:59:55 -0800 " link day.02 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Marc Reinig " link from 0894} @{i}<moose@ICO.COM> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: Axis only transformation" link subj 0545}
---
@{i}>> Does anyone know if it is possible to put a user gadget on the bottom of the
@{ui}@{i}>> screen  in Imagine 3.0 so that when you use the move, scale and rotate
@{ui}@{i}>> buttons the transformation is only applied to the axis like when using the
@{ui}
@{i}>Try pressing Shift and then the S, R, or M key (Scale, Rotate, or Move) or
@{ui}@{i}>clicking one of the functions and clicking the Loc button.
@{ui}
Pressing the Shift and S, R,or M key will move the axis, but using the Loc
button applies the S, R, and M functions to the object relative to the
object axis instead of the world axis.

-Marco


