Hi Tom ...

 >> Copying an object doesn't make you an artist!
 TR> Ouch!  Those who don't study television are doomed to repeat it! But
 TR> seriously, if you don't learn from experience (yours or anyody's),
 TR> where do you get your ideas?

I have some seriously damaged friends (Anders Rasmussen, also present in
here) and we try to come up with some strange idears sometimes. for
instance, try to Imagine a world with fog and dusty atmosphere. Then, add
mechanical elements such as a floor made out of industrial gear and huge
chains pulling this gear. Now, add oil-lamps in the corners of the scenario
and tell me what you think!

- I get my idears while sleeping, sometimes I wake up and write down a good
idea on paper and when it's morning I'll have a busy day getting home
starting to model!

