@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Sun, 4 Feb 1996 13:50:23 -0700 " link day.04 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Roger Straub " link from 1195} @{i}<straub@CSN.NET> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: Particle Question" link subj 1156}
---
On Sun, 4 Feb 1996, Mikael Johannsen wrote:

@{i}> Hi.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> Does anyone knows why some parts of the object goes through ground zero when
@{ui}@{i}> using either particles or shredder stage fx?
@{ui}
Because Imagine doesn't have true collision detection. The Shredder or
Particle FX "guesses" - it figures the approximate size of the chunk it's
moving, and draws an Imagine-ary sphere around the chunk and uses that
for bounce calculations.

@{i}>
