Hey,

        Well, I just tried it.  And lemme say outright that I may be
over-simplifying the case--but it worked like a peach for me.

        Firstly, why did you IMPORT a cube?  The lack of this primitive
is made up for so easily with the extrude command, where's the need?

        Secondly, why transform your "wall," when a simple locked scale
will do the trick?  (This is why I didn't jump into the fray when you
first mentioned your problem:  it seemed SO complicated).  But maybe
we're making it more complicated than it need be?

        OK.  I made my "wall" pretty much to your scale, 100 long, 12
high and 4 deep.  Oh, and BEFORE I did any scaling, I had already applied
the bricks texture, leaving everything default.

        When rendered, I got two half-rows of three bricks each.  Isn't
that sort of what you wanted.  With a simple movement of the texture
axis, seems like you'd have a single row of three bricks, right?

        Was it the luck of the Irish, or am I missing something?


