@node 0172 "Message number 0172"

@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Mon, 5 Feb 1996 00:51:46 GMT " link day.05 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Mark Kelly " link from 0933} @{i}<obscure@MARQUE1.DEMON.CO.UK> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: Light textures" link subj 0977}
@{i}              <IMAGINE@SJUVM.STJOHNS.EDU>) (on Sun, 04 Feb 96 13:16:43)
@{ui}---
Greetings, oscar.

@{i}> I recently modeled a space station and added the rectwind texture for
@{ui}@{i}> lights to give it scale.  Seems that when I quickrender, the lights
@{ui}@{i}> appear fine, small, like I want them, but when I trace, they all get
@{ui}@{i}> fuzzy, larger, and blockier.  I tried messy around with the antialiasing
@{ui}@{i}> rays per pixel setting in preferences, but no setting, low or high,
@{ui}@{i}> helps.  Can this be a DOF setting problem.  I haven't changed the
@{ui}@{i}> setting of the camera at all from the default values.
@{ui}
I don't know if it is your problem or not, but try setting the prefs
variable OLDA  "use old anti-alias in trace" to true. I had the same
problem (v3). I just assumed that the new alias routine caused the
problem with trace, or why would there be a prefs option?

Anyway, it worked here! :-)

Mark
