@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Mon, 5 Feb 1996 09:10:45 -0500 " link day.05 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Bob Sampson " link from 0307} @{i}<RobSampson@AOL.COM> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: Fonts Question" link subj 0757}
---
In a message dated 96-02-05 08:16:46 EST, you write:

@{i}>Could someone explain to me (simply!)
@{ui}@{i}>how to use font-letters as objects
@{ui}@{i}>in Imagine 3.0...?
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}>I notice there is a setup parameter
@{ui}@{i}>asking for the directory of Postscipt
@{ui}@{i}>Fonts, but I'm not even sure what
@{ui}@{i}>a Postscript font is... Is it different
@{ui}@{i}>to the standard WIndows fonts..?
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}>--
@{ui}@{i}>Cliff
@{ui}
First you have to obtain the fonts you need in order to make this work.  I
have heard there are archives of such on aminet and someone may be able to
give you directions on how to obtain them, or you can call Mike's BBS in
California (805-683-1388) and pull archives psfonts1.zip thru psfonts3.zip.
 Inside my Imagine directory I put a directory called fonts and placed all
the fonts inside.  Then go to prefs and change the path accordingly.  In my
case the drive is E: and the imagine directory is im30 to I put in prefs
E:\im30\fonts.  Then go to the spline editory and load fonts.  Choose the
style you want, type in the message and accept.  Choose add points, faces and
bevel you desire and then choose save points.  Save to an object directory in
whatever project you are working in.  Go to detail editor and load the font
object.  You will have a grouped object.  Take it from there.  Hope this
helps you out.

Bob.............
