David:

-        I thought TV2 was using Imagine in their regular graphics fare.  You
-are of course right.  It would be waay cool to see some commercial uses of
-Imagine.  Perhaps some of the other members of the list could mention when
-Imagine is used in a commercial animation setting.

Yes, we use Imagine for our regular 3d graphics, and people in the trade here in
Norway are quite impressed by the quality we deliver, and when they ask what we
use, they are stunned.
But we do not do comercials, we only do inhouse promotion, show title animations
and so forth.
But we are about to expand our graphic arsenal by bying Lightwave for our 3
SGI-Onyx boxes. That does however not mean that we are skipping Imagine, it
means that we increase our tool box.

Tom R G


