---
Surfing the web the other day I came across this rather nifty site that has
lots of tileable textures freely available. There are 120+ normal textures,
bricks, wood, stones etc., and 160+ abnormal textures, you know, the ones
everyone likes to use for webpage backgrounds and about 36 that are
unclassified. The address is.

http://www.meat.com

You will need a browser that can show jpeg pictures as well as the ability
to save pictures out of the pages a-la netscape as well as a reasonably fast
connection. On the other hand you can FTP the textures from them but I'm not
sure of the address.

Have fun.
Chris Hall.

