---
On Wed, 7 Feb 1996, Dave Wilson wrote:

@{i}>                         Hello.  I have two seperate yet related problems
@{ui}@{i}> with transparent stuff.  First, I'm trying to use a brush map to apply a
@{ui}@{i}> texture to an object.   I need certain parts of this texture to be absent so
@{ui}@{i}> I've colored them black (and white) to be able to set the genlock feature to
@{ui}@{i}> make that section of the image transparent.  This isn't working with either
@{ui}@{i}> color.  The closet I got was by setting filter settings but that just makes
@{ui}@{i}> it look as though theres been holes cut in my object.  What am I doing wrong
@{ui}@{i}> here?
@{ui}
The genlock doesn't work on a specific colour per say what it does is
make the background colour of your image the transparent area.  If you
would like black to be the transparent part, make sure black is the
background colour of the image when you cut or save it.


