What you need to do to make you background transparent for your web (using
paint shop pro) is
save the file as a gif, select version 89a-interlaced and then click the
options button. This
will open a transpancy dialog box, then you can choose the background or a
specific pal number
for the transparency.  (Yes it's that easy)

Warrick Holfeld

Imagine 4.0, PC P90 , 32Mb ram, beginer+ user.

