On Thu, 8 Feb 1996, Cliff Bradshaw wrote:

@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> It all seems to have gone *rather* quiet on the subject of the
@{ui}@{i}> Grassroots Manual.  The last thing I recall was the guy who was
@{ui}@{i}> supposed to be collecting material said he was leaving the list...
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> It would be a shame for such an obviously *brilliant* idea
@{ui}@{i}> (and probably one of the few examples of PC and Amiga users
@{ui}@{i}> working in harmony(?) on the Internet) to fall apart due to lack
@{ui}@{i}> of organisation.  At the very least, it should serve to lessen the
@{ui}@{i}> traffic on the IML from complete newcomers without manuals. (Guilty).
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> So who is actually running this project now...?  I'm sure many people
@{ui}@{i}> would be willing to collect material and bung it all together - I
@{ui}@{i}> know I would (even though I know zilch about Imagine at the moment -
@{ui}@{i}> coverdisk and all that).
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> Can we have a recap of the Grassroots Manual Progress...?
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> --
@{ui}@{i}> Cliff
