Thanks for the suggestion, The folowing is the list of those who will
contribute with the grass root manual in an Administrative Way, Such as
proff reading, conversions, archiveing, etc.

@{i}> >> Perry Lucas             Index, Sorting, & Compiling
@{ui}@{i}> >> Sharky                  Site for HTML & FTP
@{ui}@{i}> >> Matthew Clemence        A LateX version (if helped)
@{ui}@{i}> >> Gavin Lipscombe         Proff Reading and Clarity testing
@{ui}@{i}> >> Larry Fuller            Proff Reading
@{ui}@{i}> >> Tom Ross                Proff Reading.
@{ui}@{i}> >> Ian E. Petersen         Will make an Acrobat version
@{ui}@{i}> >> Ernesto Poveda          Convetr . TXT to .guide (for the amiga ver.)
@{ui}@{i}> >> M. Cheng                Can help on the TeX version.
@{ui}@{i}> >> Torgeir Holm            Graphic design and layot on an acrobat version.
@{ui}
I thank you all again, please don't feel discouraged by those "No Way"
messages, It's hard, but what ever is done is great!

I think we need more experts writeing on Imagine subjects, Soon I'll
post the addresses of the contributors, so people doing the same thing
can agree on sharing the job.

 Also note that
David gallegos has an analysis of the Imagine 3.0 reference manual at:
http://www.west.net/~orfevre/index.htm

If some one wants the index perry proposed, I have it and can e mail it
(privately if you agree)

 and

Dave Thompson knows a forms expert, who may write that part.


Thanks in advence!
Thanks to all the volunteers!


