@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Phil Stopford " link from 1116} @{i}<pstopfor@jesus.ox.ac.uk> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: Bye for now (fwd)" link subj 0598}
---
This was posted by Perry as you can see, it tells you everything.

---------- Forwarded message ----------
Date: Tue, 23 Jan 1996 19:04:53 -0500
From: Perry Lucas <plucas@VT.EDU>
To: Multiple recipients of list IMAGINE <IMAGINE@SJUVM.STJOHNS.EDU>
Subject: Re: Bye for now

Their are several option instead of unsubscribing from the list:

One is to set youself to digest so you'll only receive one mail message a day.
To do this,

Send Mail message to:  Listserv@sjuvm.stjohns.edu
Body of Message     :  Set Imagine Digest

Or, you can turn off mail delivery until you return by setting yourself to
nomail
and reactivating it when you return, to do this

Send mail message to:  Listserv@sjuvm.stjohns.edu
Body of message     :  Set Imagine nomail

Reactivate:

Body of Message     :  Set Imagine mail

--Perry

