@{i}>Did you ever try modelling anatomy with metaballs (blobs) ? Did you ever get
@{ui}@{i}>yourself an "anatomy for artists" book and try to model bones or muscles ?
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}
I haven't tried the blobs yet. Sounds really promising though.
Yeah I do have lots of Anatomy books, and I draw from them, and study putting
together humans with anatomical knowledge, for my painting and drawing.
Certainly any ability I have discovered in 3D modelling of Humans comes
directly from this.

@{i}>I am thinking about building an anatomy kit with certain parts that can be
@{ui}@{i}>`sewn together'.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}
I've been thinking the same thing ! My specialty would be heads, I think,
that looked different from one another, like people. I have an interesting
one going right now, with eyeballs that are made to ray-trace with good
realistic highlight effects at any angle, accomplished with no texture maps
(it really works!). I also like trying to create lower-polygon human models
which still render well, and look natural, not too muscular.

@{i}>Do you have any interest in architecture ? That's were perspective
@{ui}@{i}>projections really shine.
@{ui}
Yes, I do. But I've spent so much time experimenting with the lighting and
textures, I haven't done much about the spaces themselves. They've been kept
simple so far.

@{i}> Same idea - build a kit of basic shapes like walls, pillars,
@{ui}@{i}>windows in a CAD program, transfer to a 3D modeller for lighting, texturing
@{ui}@{i}>and camera moves. I would be especially interested in historical models like
@{ui}@{i}>temples, churches, palaces ... Ever heard of any efforts to make such a kit
@{ui}@{i}>or sell it ?
@{ui}
No, I haven't. But It's obviously a GREAT timesaving idea. I've tried a
couple cheap CAD programs, but there's always something wrong with them. Like
the dxf saving is poor. Or the features are too limited. I have always been
interested in using a CAD prog. for making human cross-sections to load into
Imagine for skinning. But the progs I've seen have had terrible bezier
features, and of course this would be needed for decent cross-sections
Any ideas as to where to find a decent cheap (shareware, maybe ?) CAD
program?
Bob, are you listening?

Nancy
