@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: Ehhh.." link subj 0687}
---
The problem with Tom's FLC's is that he created them in Imagine.
Therefore you need to play them back in Imagine if you don't want
the sparkles.  Imagine doesn't create proper FLC's.  You need to
compile the individual frames with an outside program like DTA if
you want them to look good on all players.  By the way,  his GATE
FLC is very nice.

Jim Shinosky.

