@node 0461 "Message number 0461"

@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Mon, 12 Feb 1996 17:40:33 -0500 " link day.12 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Jim Shinosky " link from 0783} @{i}<tracker@EN.COM> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: Ehhh.." link subj 0687}
---
You don't have to create any projects to view a FLC in Imagine.
Just go to the detail editor and pull down the file menu.  There
is a play FLC requester there.

On Mon, 12 Feb 1996, Granberg Tom wrote:

@{i}> Dave Wilson:
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> By the way, what the heck should I use to view your
@{ui}@{i}> >anims?  They just sparkle shades of blue and I can barely make out whats
@{ui}@{i}> >happening.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> Just make a project in Imagine, then a subproject, and move the file you want
@{ui} to
@{i}> see into that subproject. Open the project, load the subproject, and load the
@{ui}@{i}> anim. Then play!
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> PS.One anim at the time, you cant have two anim files in the same subproject
@{ui}@{i}> dir.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> Tom
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}

