@{ui}Maybe you don't have any oscillator clock connected to the FPU. If your card
takes an FPU, then it sholdn't matter if it's a 68881 or 882, they are pin
compatible. I guess that you have a PLCC-socket, so have you inserted it
the right way (index corner to index of socket). Boy, would I love to have
a FPU (working of course). If you get it to work, then I would definitly
go for your alternative #5 (I myself has about the same configuration, and
it works for me, though you can never have too much memory or processor power).

