@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Wed, 14 Feb 1996 15:44:54 +1000 " link day.14 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Stuart Fletcher " link from 1261} @{i}<stuartf@HERO.LIB.DELM.TAS.GOV.AU> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Lights and Shadows" link subj 0352}
---
This may seem like a stupid question but it has got me confused.

I have created a scene with a series of columns in a semi-circle
and a glowing orb at the centre of the circle. The glowing orb has
got an axis that I made a light source (L1) positioned at its centre.
Also placed in the scene is another light source (L2) of the the right
side of the camera, this light was placed in the stage editor.
refer to ascii diagram below.

                             o
                          o     o
                        o    L1   o
                       o           o

                                             L2


                             \/
                           camera

L1 and L2 are both lights of diminishing intesity with the same intesity
values, L2 is the only shadow casting light source.

Initially I ray-traced the scene only using the Light L1, I then added
L2 but when the ray trace was complete the shadows from L2 had darkened
the surfaces that had previously been fully illuminated by L1.

What is going on, if L2 was of greater intensity than L1 you should be able
to see shadows, but the shadows cast by L2 should not darken areas
that are illuminated by L1.

Hopefully I have explained this enough because it has confused the hell out of
 me.


Regards

Stuart Fletcher
stuartf@hero.delm.tas.gov.au
