@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Wed, 14 Feb 1996 23:52:22 -0500 " link day.14 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Charles Blaquiere " link from 0396} @{i}<blaq@IO.ORG> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Postscript fonts (was: Starting)" link subj 0448}
---
On Wed, 14 Feb 1996, Harry Drummond wrote:

@{i}> One question of my own: I load fonts but then get told they're not loaded,
@{ui}@{i}> so I don't get any further. Am I missing a simple installation procedure, or
@{ui}@{i}> does an Adobe font manager have to be present as well as the fonts?
@{ui}
Imagine only supports Type 1 fonts that use the standard Adobe encoding
vector. Search for the string "/Encoding StandardEncoding def"; if it
isn't there, the font won't work with Imagine.


