@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Fri, 16 Feb 1996 10:05:22 -0500 " link day.16 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Bob Sampson " link from 0307} @{i}<RobSampson@AOL.COM> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Simple things" link subj 1571}
---
Well it seems the little things Imagine does will never stop amazing me.
 Although probably everyone but me realized this, I found that I could select
individual faces of an object and extrude just them.  I had not ever thought
about it before nor needed to do so, but the project I'm working on now lent
itself to this technique.  Specifically I wanted to modify the eye sockets in
a head object I'm creating for a scene so that they would be deeper and
recessed.  I was going to merge a tube and then manipulate the points when I
figured I would just try extruding a select set of faces on the object.  It
worked and the modeling came out better than I could of hoped for.  I know
the guru's on the list may read this and laugh because they have been doing
this for years or something but I figured new user's might benefit from my
recent education:)

Bob.............
