@node 0602 "Message number 0602"

@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Fri, 16 Feb 1996 09:36:48 -0800 " link day.16 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Mike McCool " link from 1006} @{i}<mikemcoo@EFN.ORG> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: [Q] defining "Gold" texture" link subj 1445}
---
Gold is really just gold-chrome, which means it's completely reflective.
The trick with metal textures is to set up something in your environment for
them to REFLECT.  Some kind of global brushmap is in order.


