Hello All,

        I thought you all might be interested in hearing that I've
got Imagine runing on an SGI Indigo2 122MHz computer.  Yes, Imagine,
which won't run under Windows 95, is now running happily on an
SGI.

        Before you all drool all over your keyboards or hunt me
down out of envy, you should know it is running about the same speed
as a 386...

        So, how did I achieve this miricle?  Well, a little program
called SoftWindows.  It is a complete 486 PC computer running in a
window on the SGI desktop.

        Unless you have one kick-ass SGI, Imagine will ALWAYS run
faster on a PC or Amiga.   With Impulse's new "bleed them dry" pricing
policy, I would hate to see what they would charge for a native SGI
version of Imagine. :-)

Later,

Chris.

