@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Sun, 18 Feb 1996 00:04:43 +0930 " link day.18 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"travis " link from 1399} @{i}<envision@DARWIN.TOPEND.COM.AU> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: [Q] defining "Gold" texture" link subj 1445}
---
@{i}>I'm attempting to create an object in solid gold.  When I
@{ui}@{i}>select the "Gold" texture from the attributes requester
@{ui}@{i}>it comes out looking green!  Do I need to select the Gold
@{ui}@{i}>texture *then* set the R,G,B values to Gold? (204,127,50
@{ui}@{i}>I think...)  That's what I did anyway and it still looks
@{ui}@{i}>green!
@{ui}
@{i}>Anyone help?
@{ui}
Have a look at the reflect values of your attributes.

A smooth surface with attributes suitable for gold will have a green caste,
esp. if you are rendering the object with a blue sky.  Turn down the reflect
values or make the surface of your object rough ( not roughness ) or bumpy.



Travis.

envision@darwin.topend.com.au
travis@topend.com.au

