considering doing some more work with metaballs, but I've experimented with
booleans, forms, skinning, splines, you name it,... and so far, point-by-point
has turned out to be best and fastest for the organic modeling I do. I couldn't
do it without my drawings though. If the geometry is well-worked-out on paper
first, building it in Imagine is alot less painless.

