@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Mon, 19 Feb 1996 19:28:35 -0500 " link day.19 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Paul Thompson " link from 1072} @{i}<shinobi@GOLD.INTERLOG.COM> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: Imagine 4,0 RotationAnimation" link subj 0857}
@{i}              Wold-Hansen" at Feb 20, 96 01:18:06 am
@{ui}---
@{i}> OK -  You may use the "Rotate2 FX", but that one doesn't
@{ui}@{i}> allow for smooth acc./decc. in and out of rotation.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> How do you do that without manual tweaking?
@{ui}
The easiest method I know of rotating with acceleration and deceleration
is to create a spiral path around the rotation point.  Add an axis and
have it follow the path.  Then you can specify acceleration and
deceleration for the axis.  Finally, have your rotating object track to
the axis.  Done.

Paul


