@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Mon, 19 Feb 1996 18:54:53 -0800 " link day.19 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Chuck Needham " link from 0445} @{i}<twobit@GLOBALDIALOG.COM> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: OctVolume ???" link subj 1111}
---
Robert Smith wrote:
@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> When doing a raytrace render that's not very large I keep getting a
@{ui}@{i}> error such as "WORLD OCTVOLUME IS TOO LARGE". Can anyone explain what
@{ui}@{i}> this means and how do I get around this problem.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}
I just had the same problem this week...

All you have to do is, from the Stage Editor, select an object close to
0,0,0 and shift-select each of the other objects (including lights and
camera) until they are all selected, then scale the whole scene down to
at least 50 %. Save the changes and re-render.

Something in your scene was sticking out beyond Imagine's world limits.

If you still get the message, scale the scene down a little more.

@{i}>From the camera's point of view, nothing will have changed because it all
@{ui}was scaled together.

Hope this helps.

--
