At 07:42 PM 2/19/96 -0500, you wrote:
@{i}>I have a question, since we at Helmy Productions have moved from the
@{ui}@{i}>Amiga platform to the PC, I am just curious about one thing.  Is it
@{ui}@{i}>really true that there is no program on the PC that compares to
@{ui}@{i}>BRILLIANCE 2.0? I really find it hard to believe.  Before you say it,
@{ui}@{i}>Yes we do have Photoshop and also tried Paint Shop Pro, but we still
@{ui}@{i}>haven't found a program as great as BRILLIANCE.  If there is anyone out
@{ui}@{i}>there who knows of a program similar please let us know.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}
IMHO, the best PC paint program is Fractal Design Painter, coupled with a
pressure sensitive drawing tablet. You can chose dozens of brush types,
paper types, an "image hose", etc. The TV commercials for Coke with the
animated sun were done in Fractal, along with the X-Files intro.

