@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Tue, 20 Feb 1996 01:47:24 EST " link day.20 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{" Tim Wilson [Crestline]  " link from 0097} @{i}<76432.1122@COMPUSERVE.COM> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Reducing Render Time" link subj 1538}
---
To Jaeson Koszarsky re your Some Info message of Mon, 19 Feb 1996 15:28:22
-0500,

@{i}>>>You can also opt to use brushmaps instead of procedural textures.<<<
@{ui}        Another good timesaver, suggested also by Tom Ross. Some of the
procedural textures, especially the ones based on fractal noise, can slow
rendering quite a bit as compared to brush maps.        I think the size of the
brush map can also effect rendering time, but not necessarily in the way you'd
expect. In some circumstances, large brushmaps may actually take LESS time to
render than small ones, because no interpolation may have to be calculated to
blend the brush's pixels together.

-Tim


			@{"   Return  to  Main    " link main}
			@{"Return to Natural Index" link natural}
@endnode
