---
On Tue, 20 Feb 1996, Marc Steinkoenig wrote:

@{i}> Re: Phasers, etc.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> I like the fact that this list isn't TOO heavily moderated, as illustrated
@{ui}@{i}> by this way off-topic thread. Not to knock the thread... I think it's an
@{ui}@{i}> interesting creative discussion. I have two points to bring up.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> The first one is on topic (sorry, guys). I know that POV allows you to
@{ui}@{i}> define a lightsource as a shape. For example, as a long cylinder for
@{ui}@{i}> laser/phaser/energy weapons effects. Does Imagine have something like
@{ui}@{i}> this? Supposing we could bend the laws of reality (like they do in
@{ui}@{i}> Sci Fi) and make beams visible, how would you do it in Imagine?
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}Very simple.

First make a cylinder that corresponds to the shape you desire your light
beam to have.

Next give it a fog length.  This will allow objects to shine through the
light beam.

Of course, place one end of the cylinder at the beginning of the light.

