@{ui}
The Edimator has a 4M buffer. I assume this is what gives it the power
to smooth over any burps encountered when a non-AV drive recalibrates
itself. I dunno, how long is a drive unavailable when it recalibrates?
4M can hold a reasonable amount of video.

@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> After all this you still need a real broadcast quality recorder so that you
@{ui}@{i}> can take your masterpiece to the local TV station and have them mess with it
@{ui}@{i}> :-)
@{ui}
Or do what a friend does: rent a Betacam deck for the day, when you're
ready to do your final transfer.


