@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Wed, 21 Feb 1996 09:19:09 -0500 " link day.21 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Mike van der Sommen " link from 1023} @{i}<MikeVDS@AOL.COM> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: Divide overflow error" link subj 0635}
---
In a message dated 96-02-20 10:53:14 EST, you write:

@{i}>Ok, this is a new one.  I am raytracing a complex scene and twice now it has
@{ui}@{i}>kicked out on abnormal program termination.  This last time the message came
@{ui}@{i}>up on the dos prompt "Divide overflow error".  Anyone got any ideas of what
@{ui}@{i}>the heck is going on?
@{ui}
Last time I got Divide Overflow Errors it had to do with memory wait-state
configurations. Check your CMOS advanced chipset options. If it's set to
1 wait state, change it to 0 (or visaversa). See if that helps.

ps. Have you added more memory lately?

