At 10:26 PM 2/21/96 +1300, Bill Boyce wrote:
@{i}>At 12:26 AM 21/2/96 -0600, you wrote:
@{ui}@{i}>>I'm All for this idea! This would relieve a great deal of artistic pressures!
@{ui}@{i}>>But it would have to be a place with LOTS of Space cause there's LOTS of
@{ui}@{i}>>Imagineers waiting for this oppurtunity to display their artistic endeavours!
@{ui}@{i}>>
@{ui}@{i}>>                                rodman
@{ui}@{i}>As I understand it, ever news server holds all messages locally, so size is
@{ui}@{i}>a moot point, it doesn't really exist in one place. Could be wrong, but I'm
@{ui}@{i}>pretty surethat's how it works.
@{ui}
Hi,

You're right. It is kept locally at each server. One negative thing
about posting binaries to a usenet group is that it sooner or later is
removed from the servers as they need to free up space for new posting.
And just because you can see it on your server it doesn't mean everyone
else will see it on theirs. When this happens you can't tell someone to
get it there without someone posting it again. All in all, I prefer FTP
and WWW. And for those that can't do FTP readily there's always
FTP-by-email. Of course, there are people that can't put up pages but
still want to show the rest of the world what they've created. For those
it could be a good medium.

Regards,
Lars Nilsson
