On Tue, 20 Feb 1996, Anders Rasmussen wrote:

@{i}> Hi All.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> Just ONE question ..
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> How come there hasen't been any effects releses for Imagine? I mean stuff
@{ui}@{i}> like the particles and rotate (could sure use a v3 :). But howcome?
@{ui}@{i}> Gravity and collision would be nice! :)
@{ui}
Because Impulse hasn't told us how the FX mods work yet. They released a
document on the format for procedural textures and the TDDD object file
format, but nothing on FX, a coupla years back. It's still available on
Aminet. I guess they're holding out on the FX docs until they convert to
DLLs for Windies. Presumably, they will have a different format for
Amiga, too, so any information released now would be obsolete in about a
month.

