HAINZ, EXI, ODER SO AEHNLICH ... wrote in a Mail about "Imagine &
Cybergfx":
@{i}> I need some help for my retina z3 board. recently, i wanted to
@{ui}@{i}> change the drivers to cybergfx. Everthings works fine (with the
@{ui}@{i}> demo ver. of cybgfx), but Imagine wont. Even any screenpromotor
@{ui}@{i}> like newmode works.
@{ui}@{i}> Is there a possibility force Imagine to work with cybergfx ?
@{ui}@{i}> Should I try the newest version of cybergfx ?
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> At the moment I'm running my Amiga with Retinaemu. If anybody knows a
@{ui}@{i}> solution to my problem ..
@{ui}
You will not manage to get Imagine working _properly_ with CyberGFX.

You will manage to get it working, albeit with display corruption,
no state or stage anims and a host of other fubars.

It appears that Impulse in their infinite wisdom don't want to support
the Amiga retargetable graphics standard, they would sooner support
several out of date cards by writing specific segments of code for
each card.

I suggest you contact MikeH directly and ask him to support
CyberGFX.

My interest in Imagine has waned somewhat.

Cheers,

Doug.
