---
@{i}>About my caustic-question:
@{ui}
@{i}>Mike McCool and Tom Ross recommended using some Essence texture.
@{ui}
@{i}>Well, problem is that I don't have Essence. And while I'm sure that they are
@{ui}@{i}>great textures I don't have any plans on buying them.
@{ui}
@{i}>So, if you guys and guyas don't mind; any other ideas for caustics?
@{ui}
Just a thought, Havn't tried it myself.

Something like the wormvein texture on a large plane above your scene.  Maybe
even a ground object.  Then apply the transpar texture to convert from colour
(color for you Americans :-) ) to transperancy.  Place a light above the
plane/ground object so that the light is projected to your scene below
through the wormvein/transpar combination. If you thnk about it the colours
(colors :-) ) used on thw wormvein texture should be black/white.

Sounds like it would work in theory.

Travis.

