@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Fri, 23 Feb 1996 09:03:00 -0800 " link day.23 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"John Prusinski " link from 0806} @{i}<jprusins@CYBERGRAFIX.COM> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: Upper case "X" bug(?) in Spline editor" link subj 1383}
---
@{i}>> Has anyone else noticed that the upper case "X" when entering text into the
@{ui}@{i}>> Add Font requester (PC) is apparently defined as a hotkey to erase all the
@{ui}@{i}>> text you've entered in the requester?
@{ui}

@{i}>For the PC Impulse has mapped the right shift and right alt keys to act like
@{ui}@{i}>a Right Amiga key. Therefore I think this is what might be causing the problem.
@{ui}@{i}>[ They added the string clearing function to be consistent. ]
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}>Have you tried using the left shift key when typing the upper case. If you have
@{ui}@{i}>and you still have the problem - then - RATS!!!!.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}>You also might try the capslock key. If you havn't.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}
@{i}>Robin Luiten
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}
It WORKED! Thanks, Robin.  I had tried capslock, with no success, but it
turns out that using the left shift key is the solution.  (I rendered the
word "HEXEN" in honor of the game, as a test!)
I'm still a bit annoyed that it never occurred to the programmers that using
any shift key as a remap from a function key might cause problems with text
entry... but hey :^)

John.
