---
@{i}>I have a question, do you know a good solution to get all my Amiga files
@{ui}over to
@{i}>my new P133, I dont want to use a zillion disk's!!!!
@{ui}
@{i}>Tom R G
@{ui}
Hi Tom,
This subject has been covered a bunch of times here, but I suspect that you
(like me) don't tend to pay attention to subjects until you need them :>)
A couple of possible solutions: Link-It, a serial port connection from
Legendary Designs, works transparently and well, but is SLOOOOOOW (not a
problem if you just want to set up the file copy and leave it to run
overnight).  About US$100 as I recall.  Or my current favorite, 88 Meg
PC-formatted Syquest cartridges using CrossDOS on the Amiga... a lot faster,
especially if you don't have a gigabyte or so of files to transfer.

John.


