@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Neat lighting trick." link subj 0377}
---
Hi, all.  Seeing as how the current contest topic is lighting, I thought
I'd throw a neat little trick out.

Did you know that you can use *negative* values for light intensity so
lights actually subtract light from a scene?  I can't get it to work in
3.0 for some reason but it works great in 4.0.

Anybody know why it doesn't work in 3.0?

Happy tracing.

        -Martin

