Carlos Martinez wrote:
@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> Hello, I4ve got a little problem, when I put a repeat bump map over a
@{ui}@{i}> plane for example, I don4t know why the limits of the image make bump
@{ui}@{i}> too, the same thing when you put a warp bump map over a ball, you rotate
@{ui}@{i}> the ball and you can see the join of the image, there are some solution.
@{ui}@{i}> thanks a lot, Carlos
@{ui}
Ya know? I'm having the same problem. I had several calls into Impulse
about it, they took down the info (I expect).

This same problem was in Silver's first version. I called support, sent
some samples of global wrapped maps, and they fixed the problem in the
next upgrade. It was a problem with the way DPaint stored bitmaps and
they had just hired a new programmer who had used old code.

Imagine had it right in version 1 and 2, but then when version 3 came
out....WHAT!...I loaded my map in and rotated the globe, there was a
problem. I haven't checked version 4 yet to see if the same thing occurs.

It's been quite some time since I called Impulse about it, but it is a
MAJOR problem (IMHO), especially when you want to rotate a globe with
elevation maps, ...there's one nasty stair-step on the leading edge of
the map.

I really believe it is something that should be attended to, if the
haven't fixed it in 4.0.

--
