@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Mon, 26 Feb 1996 12:04:02 -0600 " link day.26 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Rick Beilfuss " link from 1142} @{i}<vview@CSWNET.COM> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: how do i extrude in 3 dimensions?" link subj 1472}
---
@{i}>I want to take a sphere, with a hole in it, and extrude it while expanding the
@{ui} sphere.

Your question is a little confusing. A sphere is a 3d object and
"extruding" is usually used to mean taking a 2d object and expanding it
into the 3rd dimension. To enlarge a sphere you would "scale" it. If you
want to "drill" a hole through it, you would use a cylinder and "slice"
it. If none of these is what you want to do, then a little more
explanation is in order.

Rick


