Howdy,

I guess it's possible, but I wouldn't count on that either. Just take a
look at the number of 3d party offerings, and since Impulse obviously
sits on the source to their own textures, it's probably easier for them
to convert them to DLLs (once done for one the process for the rest
should be fairly quick).

And since they have said they'll release the format for textures and
effects anyone seriuosly wanting to take advantage of Imagine for
Windows shouldn't find it difficult to follow suit. Heck, compiling a
DLL is like slicing bread compared to compiling textures as it is
right now, with Phar Lap's linker being a requirement (as far as I know).

Regards,
Lars Nilsson
