In a message dated 96-02-26 01:21:47 EST, Jon Rubin wrote about the Edimator:

@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}>I wouldn't put much stock in the capabilities of this video card, since it
@{ui}@{i}>uses an ISA slot, which isn't capable of anything near full-frame video.
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}
The Edimator uses a SCSI controller interface built into the board for a
dedicated SCSI drive. It is the drive that records and plays back the video,
bypassing the ISA connection. The Edimator comes complete with a gang of
input and output connectors for playback on a television monitor, not the
computer monitor.

