Nancy Jacobs wrote:
@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> Does anyone know of a DECENT piece of email software for PC (especially 32
@{ui} bit, Windows 95). I truly despise Microsoft exchange AND
Eudora. THEY STINK !  I can

        I use Netscape Mail for all my mail.  It is really nice. Full
MIME compatability and automatically decodes inline images and files and
such.  Hundreds of times better the the crappy version of Eudora I had.
And best part is, it COMES with Netscape 2.0!  Just set it up to use
your POP client (wich is what I think most internet providers use...at
least the ones I know of) and click on the little letter icon at the
bottom-left of the Netscape window and BOOM, instant mail access.  I
can't recomend it enough.  Only problem is, if SOMEONE decides to send
upload another 3 megs of uuencoded binaries, there is no way to get
around downloading it.  I don't know if Eurdora will delete mesages off
of the server as soon as it downloads them, but Netscape mail waits
until it gets all of them.  If you crash halfway though, you have to
download all of them again.  Only time I had a problem is when SOMEONE
decided to send Imagine to everyone here on the list...and we know what
happens to people who do that! :-)

Chris.


