@{i}>At 08:28 AM 2/26/96 PST, you wrote:
@{ui}@{i}>>Is it possible to extrude in x,y,z directions?
@{ui}@{i}>>I want to take a sphere, with a hole in it, and extrude it while expanding
@{ui}@{i}>>the sphere.  Where the hole is, I want that to be a tunnel with faces.
@{ui}@{i}>>I don't want to be able to see in between the smaller and larger sphere,
@{ui}@{i}>>I want where the hole is to be closed off.  Is there an easy way of doing
@{ui}@{i}>>this?
@{ui}
I think I get it. Try extruding you sphere with hole, and joining the extruded
points to a single point in the centre, then place a sphere inside to surface
of your object and slice. Now scale the sphere(s) until they are the sizes you
require.

(I think. If I understand your description.)


