@{ui}@{i}>I think it would be good, but...
@{ui}@{i}>What about memory? both screens with different positioning of the object
@{ui}@{i}>would be loaded in chip RAM at the same tile.
@{ui}
No, all that would need to be stored would be the object positions etc, which
are internal values which are used to draw the screen, not the other way around.

So if you could live with a screen redraw, the memory hit would only be any
extra
objects - on in on place but not the other.

Personally, I could live with the Detail, Stage and Action editors all being
merged into one. I saw a Lightwave review that claimed the program was to
"modal"
referring to having two "editors", animator and modeler. They'd just LOVE
imagine.
