suitably sooty and sky filtered (255,255,255) cloud texture, but the
filter doesn't appear to be completely transparent - the cone shows up as
a grey troangle against the sky with the dark flecks that are meant to be
the smoke now looking a bit daft.
If I haven't explained it well, look on some magazine CDs and you might
find a demo of Seek and Destroy - this has a reasonable anim, but with a
superb smoke effect I'd like to duplicate - any ideas on how to defeat
the incomplete filter?

Phil.

