@{b}Date:@{ub}         @{"Wed, 28 Feb 1996 11:12:30 -0600 " link day.28 }
@{b}From:@{ub}         @{"Rick Beilfuss " link from 1142} @{i}<vview@CSWNET.COM> @{ui}
@{b}Subject:@{ub}      @{"Re: More Edge Line" link subj 1001}
---
I'm guessing here that your two tubes are at 90 degrees from each other,
and if so that's your problem. Imagine edge fill only works good on
objects somewhat lined up with each other. (if this isn't the case, must
be a bug with the Amiga version)

Make sure your tubes are somewhat lined up before joining. Then use
bones to bend the tubes to 90 degrees.

Rick


