On Wed, 28 Feb 1996, Ing. Alexander Owen Wallace wrote:

@{i}> Hi there dear imagineers!
@{ui}@{i}>
@{ui}@{i}> I have a dumb question. Is thera a way to scale a project in Imagine, like
@{ui}@{i}> haveing a 90 fgrames animation and makeing imagine evenly distribute all
@{ui}@{i}> keys on a desired number of frames, lets say 300?
@{ui}
If you're using an Amiga, which I see you're not, you can. Ian Smith's
Imagine Utilities has an AREXX script called StageFrames, which lengthens
a project by a set amount and scales all of the timelines to fit. You can
find it on Ian Smith's homepage: http://www.ncinter.net/~iansmith/

I truly can't help you on a PC, though. Anyone else? =)

@{i}>
