In the example I just gave, I was assuming that you are only mirroring the bones
of a limb like the arm or leg. That's why you ''reverse the value of the X
POSITION'' to move the mirrored set into the opposite position. Unless you're
designing some really bizarre creature, you shouldn't need a duplicate set of
vertebral bones.

