Ah, but this doesn't always work.

If you can slice the objects successfully by themselves then usually they
will slice together.

But say you have two objects that won't slice together.  Try slicing each
piece by itself.  I've done this several times.  One of your pieces probably
won't slice itself, you'll get an error.  This may only be related to the
dreaded err2 though.  So if they don't slice individually, they don't slice
together either.

