I single-frame record to a neat (and expensive!) Hi8 VTR, the Sony 9650.
With software this is controllable directly out of the Amiga serial port.
I chose it because of the lovely PCM sound, better than HiFi (which
itself is no slouch).

@{i}>From this master I make VHS HiFi sound copies which look and sound mighty
@{ui}good to me, but I lack comparisons. SVHS also possible this way.

Single-framing is probably on its way out as non-linear methods speed up.
But besides the good sound an advantage is that you can make a frame as
graphically rich as you want to without worrying about slowdowns or
memory chokes.

