@{ui}@{i}>on the network, say 3 machines. On machine 1 set up a render of the scene
@{ui}@{i}>from frame 1 to 997 at a step of 3, machine 2 set up from frame 2 to 998
@{ui}@{i}>at a step of 3, and on machine 3, frame 3 to 999 at a step of 3,
@{ui}@{i}>logically it should work. Each of the frames are rendered by
