On 28-Feb-96 19:37:27, Chris Magoulis wrote the following:
@{i}>the most cost effective manner?  Is there, perhaps, a card that I can throw
@{ui}@{i}>into my PC that will output to a VCR or something like this?
@{ui}
@{i}>     Here's my system specs:
@{ui}@{i}>       Pentium 75 PC
@{ui}@{i}>       16 MB RAM
@{ui}@{i}>       SVGA 1024KB
@{ui}@{i}>       1.2 Gig HD
@{ui}
@{i}>     So what can you guys throw at me?  I'll initially assume that I need to
@{ui}@{i}>get a LOT more memory, but what do I know?!  Any and all information is
@{ui}@{i}>greatly appreciated.
@{ui}
Well, I'm not at this trouble because I have an Amy and I just plugit into a
VHS recorder to tape it.

But, I can tell you about a friend of mine who moved from an Amy to a Pentium
to speed up his renderings and has them networked.
He renders in the PC, them moves the pics to the Amy, makes the animation at
the Amy, with a beter frame rate and direct output to his VHS.

This really works fast, because when he's adding post-rendering effects,
making the anim and taping it, the PC is already generating another anim. :)

Maybe a good card to tape the PC is cheaper than an Amy, maybe not. But since
some of you have both machines this could be a good idea.

I just hope someone finds it usefull.

